reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Awesome sound at a fair price
reviews.reviewText: Have a 2009 Fj Cruiser that had JL speakers in the dash. They would distort at louder levels real bad. Decided I had enough and purchased these. Man these sound great with ZERO distortion. Great highs and provide a descent punch for a 3.5 inch speaker. Going to replace the back pillar speakers with these next! Great product at a fantastic price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Ran some tests. 25 percent better than factory?
reviews.reviewText: I was curious to see how well the Recoil BB-T bass blockers would reduce low frequencies, and I figured I'd compare them to my factory speakers while I was at it. I plugged them into a home stereo receiver that puts out 26 watts RMS per channel, so it's in the same range as most car audio receivers. Same distance each time, 75% volume, I played the first half of a song with lots of highs and mids and a subwoofer level bassline (Offspring-Hit That). The one that has "1367" at the top is a single Pyle. "883" is a factory 5 x 7 from my Mach 460 stereo. They're supposed to be higher quality speakers than the normal Ford factory installs. "1325" is Pyle + Recoil BB-T. This is a free-air setup, no enclosure, on a not so great receiver with no EQ controls, so it's just a comparison, not an actual evaluation of the speaker's performance. The number at the top is irrelevant, that's just where the peak was when I snapped the picture.The factory speaker had more bass but the highs weren't as crisp as the Pyle. Makes sense because the factory speaker has no added tweeters. The Pyle was noticeably clearer at high frequencies but it didn't win by much. I'd estimate it's about 15% - 25% clearer/cleaner than factory. The BB-T's did exactly what I wanted and blocked almost all the bass and a lot of the mids with no significant reduction on the high end. They'll get more juice and EQ / crossover treatment in the car so I'll update this if there's a huge difference, but I'm not pulling out the Mach 460 rear mount again just to compare it to the factory speaker. I'd rather eat lint.

reviews.reviewText: I would like everybody to know that these speakers are not meant for what they're being advertised for for having 250 W of base that is false I ordered 4 to 5" speakers and got 2" speakers these are not replacement speakers these are sub Box speakers and they are not to be used with replacement for your original speakers this was falsely advertised the speakers are not very loud Definitely good quality speakers but definitely falsely advertised because they're not very big mine didn't come with the screws or clamps I got 110' power wire so I cut it in half and used it 5' for 5' it is not as expected with the cover because it was too big I was missing for screws In the outlook on this item doesn't mean any of the specifthat is advertiyes but overall the speaker's work but they are not high definition or a 100% what they were advertised at My regular cracked speakers that I was going to replace only have a base wattage of 75 and they outpush these falsely advertised speakers claiming "to have 200 what's" And everything else and my speakers came out of a 1988 Ford Bronco 2 that had been underneath water and they outperform knees in their busted. If you were gonna put these in a Box or a small radio would definitely recommend but anything else false advertisement and I definitely would not recommend these speakers because I'm a major gearhead and car enthusiast and I feel kind of misled on purpose just for sale and baited to buy these thinking that the medium quality or the high quality of 200 W for 2 speakers in a pair was a good deal turns out nothing is real online anymore you all have a nice day if you buy anything that you're trying to replace just go all out and pay the expensive price the quality last longer and chances are it's gonna be better off just to buy whatever it is For the money that it sold for

reviews.reviewTitle: Las mejores bocinas para sustituir las de fábrica
reviews.reviewText: 5 estrellas de 5: precio, claridad, potencia, compatibilidad, mejor que las originales en Nissan Versa 2017 mexicano. Las compraría de nuevo. 6 meses de uso y todo bien :)

El valor/precio es excelente, por el precio es un producto excelente, la calidad y desempeño no te decepciona, probé su sonido fuera del vehículo y tiene muy claro el sonido, las presente sin conectar en el lugar donde va la original y si queda un poco levantada (no creo que afecte cuando se coloque de regreso las cubiertas plásticas del tablero) en la esquina debido a su tamaño quedando ligeramente sobre un ducto de ventilación A/C, solo estoy esperando los cables adaptadores (No. parte 72-6514) para no cortar nada de la conexión original del vehículo (Dodge Journey 2013) ya estando colacadas pienso que desempeñarán lo bastante bien en comparación a las originales.
Perfect fit, sound great and very easy in install. Very happy with this purchase
